re for diversity and recognize that people learn at different rates. On average, most folks complete our training program in 3 months. Completion of the program leads to an offer for full-time employment at CDA as a Dev Ops resource. REQUIREMENTS The ideal candidate for this position is: o A recent college graduate with a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related major. o Authorized to work in the United States. o Less than one year of experience working for a technology company. o Willing to travel at least 50% of the time and able to relocate if necessary. If you do not meet these criteria, please do not apply for the position. TRAINING POSITION At CDA, we believe in hands on learning. We take a three pronged approach to our training program: 1. Online Training 2. Application in a Lab Environment 3. Presentation to CDA Team Training materials will be provided via online training platforms, such as PluralSight, LinkedIn Learning, and vendor direct curriculums. Access and training fees will be paid directly by CDA. Learning and understanding the topics/software platforms listed are a necessity for anyone looking to enter the DevOps field. o Microsoft Windows Server Operating System and components o Virtualization technologies (VMware/XenServer) o DevOps concepts, development, and integrations o CompTIA Security+ training and certification o Splunk o Ansible o Chef o Docker o Jenkins o Fastlane o Gradle o Maven o SonarQube o Nexus o Bitbucket (GIT) o Jira o Confluence Lab builds will be required to apply the concepts learned. Lab builds will need to be demonstrated to the CDA Team. The cost of a certification exam will be reimbursed by CDA upon achieving a passing score, the fees for failed exams will not be reimbursed. Certification exam expenses will be reimbursed in the form of a monthly expense check. After completion of our training program, candidates will be offered a full-time position with CDA. FULL-TIME DEV OPS POSITION The full time DevOps position is an entry level role in our Managed Services team and is for people who have a passion for technology and want to apply it to help customers. The DevOps position requires an individual to demonstrate the ability to quickly learn technical concepts like security, Splunk, virtualization, and script development. Soft skills are also important; CDA has a strong focus on customer success requiring good communication skills, accountability, teamwork and responsiveness. Travel is required for this position. PERKS o PC laptop and lab equipment provided o Cell phone and home internet paid by company Job Type: Full-time Pay: $40,000.00 - $50,000.00 per year Education: Bachelor's (Required) Work authorization: United States (Required) Required travel: 50% (Required) Work Location: Fully Remote Benefits: Health insurance Dental insurance Vision insurance Retirement plan Paid time off Work from home Flexible schedule Professional development assistance Visa Sponsorship Potentially Available: No: Not providing sponsorship for this job This Job Is: A good job for someone just entering the workforce or returning to the workforce with limited experience and education Schedule: Monday to Friday Company's Facebook page: www.facebook.com/CDACritical/ Benefit Conditions: Only full-time employees eligible Work Remotely: Yes ",
